problem_text:
Let G be a pro-p group that is a 3-dimensional Poincar´e duality group. Can
it contain a direct product F2 × F2 of free pro-p groups of rank 2?
If it can, then the answer to 20.117 is negative, but in the abstract case it is known
that it can not (P. H. Kropholler, M. A. Roller, J. London Math. Soc. (2), 39 (1989),
271–284).
P. Zalesskii
